Downlink Spectral Efficiency of Cell-Free Massive MIMO with Full-Pilot Zero-Forcing (Giovanni Interdonato - 29 September, 2018)
Cell-free Massive multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) ensures ubiquitous communication at high spectral efficiency (SE) thanks to increased macro-diversity as compared cellular communications. Unlike conventional precoding schemes that only suppress intra-cell interference, full-pilot zero-forcing (fpZF), introduced in [1], actively suppresses also inter-cell interference, without sharing channel state information (CSI) among the access points (APs)
