Online Learning for Position-Aided Millimeter Wave Beam Training (Vutha Va - 12 September, 2018)
Accurate beam alignment is essential for beam-based millimeter wave communications. The beam pair selection algorithm learns coarse beam directions in some predefined beam codebook, e.g., in discrete angles separated by the 3 dB beamwidths. When using 16x16 arrays at both the transmitter and receiver, it can achieve on average 1 dB gain over the exhaustive search (over 271x271 beam pairs) on the unrefined codebook within 100 time-steps with a training budget of only 30 beam pairs.
Link: https://arxiv.org/abs/1809.03014
