The use of multichannel data in estimating a set of frequencies is common for improving the estimation accuracy in array processing, structural health monitoring, wireless communications, and more. In particular, given $L$ channels, order $K\log K \left(1+\frac{1}{L}\log N\right)$ samples per channel, selected randomly from $N$ equispaced samples, suffice to guarantee with high probability exact estimation of $K$ normalized frequencies that are mutually separated by at least $\frac{4}{N}$
