Organizational networks are highly vulnerable to traffic-analysis attacks that can infer information from their communications even if they are encrypted. Our results show that the system can be used with minimal latency overhead ($\approx100$ms for $100$ clients) and is compatible with delay-sensitive applications such as VoIP
