On the Capacity of Fractal D2D Social Networks With Hierarchical Communications (Ying Chen - 10 August, 2018)
Firstly, for a fractal D2D social network with direct social communications, it is proved that the maximum capacity is $ Î\left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{n\log n}}\right) $ if a user communicates with one of his/her direct contacts randomly, where $ n $ denotes the total number of users in the network, and it can reach up to $ Î\left(\frac{1}{\log n}\right) $ if any pair of social contacts with distance $ d $ communicate according to the probability in proportion to $ d^{-Î²} $. The capacity is reduced in proportional to $ \frac{1}{\log n} $ if $ 2<Îµ<3 $, while the reduction coefficient is $ \frac{1}{n} $ if $ Îµ=3 $.
