A Multi-Gbps Unrolled Hardware List Decoder for a Systematic Polar Code (Pascal Giard - 3 February, 2017)
Polar codes are a new class of block codes with an explicit construction that provably achieve the capacity of various communications channels, even with the low-complexity successive-cancellation (SC) decoding algorithm. Post-place-and-route ASIC results for 28 nm CMOS are provided showing that this decoder can sustain a throughput greater than 10 Gbps at 468 MHz with an energy efficiency of 7.25 pJ/bit.
Link: https://arxiv.org/abs/1702.00938
