On the Capacity of the AWGN Channel with Additive Radar Interference (Sara Shahi - 30 January, 2017)
This paper investigates the capacity of a communications channel that, in addition to additive white Gaussian noise, also suffers from interference caused by a co-existing radar transmission. We also show that for very large radar interference, capacity is equal to $1/2\log (1 + S)$ and a proper-complex Gaussian input achieves it
