User Selection and Power Allocation in Full Duplex Multi-Cell Networks (Sanjay Goyal - 11 June, 2016)
Full duplex (FD) communications has the potential to double the capacity of a half duplex (HD) system at the link level. We focus on small cell systems because they are more suitable for FD operation, given practical self-interference cancellation limits.With practical self-interference cancellation, it is shown that the proposed hybrid FD system achieves nearly two times throughput improvement for an indoor multi-cell scenario, and about 65% improvement for an outdoor multi-cell scenario compared to the HD system.
